    {
      "question": "Prove that $(\\sin \\theta + \\csc \\theta)^2 + (\\cos \\theta + \\sec \\theta)^2 = 7 + \\tan^2 \\theta + \\cot^2 \\theta$.",
      "answer": "Proof",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Expand both squares using $(a+b)^2 = a^2 + b^2 + 2ab$.",
          "Group $\\sin^2 \\theta + \\cos^2 \\theta = 1$.",
          "Use $\\csc \\theta = 1/\\sin \\theta$ and $\\sec \\theta = 1/\\cos \\theta$ to simplify $2\\sin \\theta \\csc \\theta$ and $2\\cos \\theta \\sec \\theta$.",
          "Use $\\csc^2 \\theta = 1 + \\cot^2 \\theta$ and $\\sec^2 \\theta = 1 + \\tan^2 \\theta$.",
          "Combine all constants."
        ],
        "derivation": "(\\sin^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta + 2) + (\\cos^2 \\theta + \\sec^2 \\theta + 2) = (\\sin^2 \\theta + \\cos^2 \\theta) + 4 + (1 + \\cot^2 \\theta) + (1 + \\tan^2 \\theta) = 1 + 4 + 1 + 1 + \\tan^2 \\theta + \\cot^2 \\theta = 7 + \\tan^2 \\theta + \\cot^2 \\theta."
