    {
      "question": "If $\\tan \\theta + \\sin \\theta = m$ and $\\tan \\theta - \\sin \\theta = n$, prove that $m^2 - n^2 = 4\\sqrt{mn}$.",
      "answer": "Proof",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Calculate $m^2 - n^2 = (m+n)(m-n)$.",
          "Substitute values to find $m+n = 2\\tan \\theta$ and $m-n = 2\\sin \\theta$.",
          "Find $m^2 - n^2 = 4 \\tan \\theta \\sin \\theta$.",
          "Calculate $4\\sqrt{mn} = 4\\sqrt{(\\tan \\theta + \\sin \\theta)(\\tan \\theta - \\sin \\theta)}$.",
          "Simplify the root using $\\tan^2 \\theta - \\sin^2 \\theta$."
        ],
        "derivation": "m^2 - n^2 = (\\tan \\theta + \\sin \\theta)^2 - (\\tan \\theta - \\sin \\theta)^2 = 4 \\tan \\theta \\sin \\theta. \\text{ Also, } 4\\sqrt{(\\tan^2 \\theta - \\sin^2 \\theta)} = 4\\sqrt{\\tan^2 \\theta(1 - \\cos^2 \\theta)} = 4\\sqrt{\\tan^2 \\theta \\sin^2 \\theta} = 4 \\tan \\theta \\sin \\theta."
      },
