      "question": "Prove that $\\frac{\\tan \\theta}{1 - \\cot \\theta} + \\frac{\\cot \\theta}{1 - \\tan \\theta} = 1 + \\sec \\theta \\csc \\theta$.",
      "answer": "Proof",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Convert all terms to $\\sin \\theta$ and $\\cos \\theta$.",
          "Simplify the complex fractions.",
          "Find a common denominator.",
          "Use the identity $a^3 - b^3 = (a-b)(a^2 + ab + b^2)$.",
          "Simplify the expression to the final form."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{\\frac{\\sin}{\\cos}}{1 - \\frac{\\cos}{\\sin}} + \\frac{\\frac{\\cos}{\\sin}}{1 - \\frac{\\sin}{\\cos}} = \\frac{\\sin^2}{\\cos(\\sin-\\cos)} - \\frac{\\cos^2}{\\sin(\\sin-\\cos)} = \\frac{\\sin^3 - \\cos^3}{\\sin \\cos(\\sin-\\cos)} = \\frac{(\\sin-\\cos)(\\sin^2+\\cos^2+\\sin \\cos)}{\\sin \\cos(\\sin-\\cos)} = \\frac{1+\\sin \\cos}{\\sin \\cos} = \\sec \\theta \\csc \\theta + 1."
